Coronavirus travel health
Check the latest information on risk from COVID-19 for Moldova on the TravelHealthPro website
See the TravelHealthPro website for further advice on travel abroad and reducing spread of respiratory viruses during the COVID-19 pandemic.
You should contact local authorities for information on testing facilities.
International travel
From 21 March there will be a limited re-opening of Moldovan airspace for flights into and out of Romania from Chisinau International Airport, with some regular passenger flights resuming. You should check with your airline before travelling, and be aware that restrictions may be re-introduced at short notice.
The nearest airport outside of Moldova with direct flights to the UKis in Lasi, Romania, which is 50km from the Sculeni border crossing in the Ungheni District of Moldova. Land Borders Checkpoints with Romania are fully operational. Check with your travel company or airline for the latest information.
